HEADWORD: grounder
<hw>grounder</hw> <pr>(ground"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Baseball)</fld> <def>A batted ball that hits the ground before it
leaves the infield, or the act of hitting a baseball along the ground;
also called <altname>ground ball</altname>; -- contrasted with
<contr>fly</contr> or <contr>fly ball</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> .</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

